I do enjoy the UU church I attend but admit that I probably would not have joined if we hadn't started a family.  I also admit that the terms &quot;church&quot; and &quot;sermon&quot; do carry baggage from other organized religions for me.  But I've chosen to concentrate on the content of the organization, not the name.<br>
Below are the Principles and Purposes of UU from the UUA website.  I embrace the these statements and feel that exposing my son to a community of people who share these convictions can only do him good.  Whether or not he chooses to continue as a UU when he's an adult will be up to him.  I would also support his choice to join another organized religion.  Understand that supporting his choice would not mean agreeing with it or being happy about it.<br>
<br>
