<br>
But finally, I think that perhaps we (UUs) are running from the words &quot;belief&quot;, &quot;faith&quot;, and even &quot;worship&quot; needlessly.  I don't believe in a higher power, but I do believe in things, not least the 7 principles of UUism; I have faith in things.  Can an atheist not have a proscribed set of beliefs as well?  <br>
